  "helpFaqTitle": "Help & FAQ",
  "helpFaqIntro": "Common questions about backing up, moving to a new phone, and how your keys work.",
  "helpFaqBackupsGroup": "Backups",
  "helpFaqBackupHowQ": "How do I back up my wallet?",
  "helpFaqBackupHowA": "Open your wallet, go to its details, and tap Export to save a backup file. Keep it somewhere safe and private. When your phone's system backup is on (iCloud on iPhone, Google on Android), the app also keeps an automatic copy there.\n\nAnyone who has your backup file AND your password can access your funds — treat both like cash.",
  "helpFaqRestoreHowQ": "How do I restore from a backup?",
  "helpFaqRestoreHowA": "When adding a wallet, choose Import wallet → Tibane backup, open your backup file (or paste the JSON), and enter the wallet's password. When it finishes, tap \"Set up now\" to create this phone's signing key with a 2FA code.",
  "helpFaqRestoredCantSendQ": "I restored from a backup file but I can't send — why?",
  "helpFaqRestoredCantSendA": "A backup file never contains a signing key (it's device-only for security), so a restore alone can't sign. Finish with \"Set up this device\": a quick 2FA verification creates a signing key on this phone. Until then, sending is blocked — if you try to send you'll see a \"Set up\" shortcut that takes you there.\n\n(Moving with \"Transfer to new device\" instead brings the signing key with it, so that path needs no extra setup.)",
  "helpFaqMovingPhoneGroup": "Moving to a new phone",
  "helpFaqMoveWalletQ": "How do I move my wallet to a new phone?",
  "helpFaqMoveWalletA": "If you still have the old phone, use Transfer to new device — it's the smoothest way. On the old phone open the wallet and tap \"Transfer to new device\" to show a QR code; on the new phone choose \"Receive from another device\" and scan it, then enter the password. The signing key travels securely between the phones, so no 2FA code is needed.\n\nIf you only have a backup file, restore it on the new phone and then \"Set up this device\".",
  "helpFaqTwoPhonesQ": "Can I use the same wallet on two phones at the same time?",
  "helpFaqTwoPhonesA": "A wallet's signing key lives on one phone at a time. When you \"Set up this device\" on a new phone, that phone becomes the wallet's signing device and the previous phone will need to be set up again before it can sign. Plan to sign from one phone.",
  "helpFaqShareErrorQ": "My backup file gives an error about a \"share\" or \"party key\".",
  "helpFaqShareErrorA": "That backup is out of date. Every time a wallet is set up on a device its keys are refreshed, which makes older backup files stale. Export a FRESH backup from the phone that currently works, then import that one. Don't use \"Repair 2FA key\" with an old file — it can push a stale key and break the phone that's working.",
  "helpFaqPassword2faGroup": "Password & 2FA",
  "helpFaqChangePasswordQ": "How do I change my password?",
  "helpFaqChangePasswordA": "Go to Settings → Security & Privacy → Change password. You'll confirm the change with a 2FA code.",
  "helpFaqForgotPasswordQ": "I forgot my password.",
  "helpFaqForgotPasswordA": "Open the wallet's details (or Security & Privacy) and choose \"Forgot password? Reset via 2FA\". Verify with a 2FA code and set a new password.",
  "helpFaqWhat2faQ": "What is the 2FA key, and what does \"Repair 2FA key\" do?",
  "helpFaqWhat2faA": "Your 2FA key is a recovery key tied to your email or phone number. It's used to recover or repair a wallet — not for everyday signing. If setting up a restored wallet gets stuck (\"participant stopped responding\"), your 2FA key may be out of sync; \"Repair 2FA key\" re-syncs it from your backup so setup can finish. Only repair from the phone whose wallet currently works.",
  "helpFaqSigningSecurityGroup": "Signing & security",
  "helpFaqWhySignEveryTimeQ": "Why does every send ask for my password and fingerprint/face?",
  "helpFaqWhySignEveryTimeA": "Your wallet is protected by three keys, and any two are needed to approve a transaction: this phone's key (unlocked with your fingerprint or face) plus your password. There is no \"unlock once\" — every transaction is approved on its own, so a lost or stolen phone can't sign without your password.",
  "securityChangePasswordTitle": "Change password",
  "securityChangePasswordSubtitle": "Set a new password. You'll need your current one.",
